---
---

<section
  class="page-hero"
  style="
      background-color: var(--color-surface);
      border-bottom: 1px solid var(--color-border);
      padding-top: var(--sp-9);
      padding-bottom: var(--sp-8);
    "
>
  <div class="app-container" style="text-align: center;">
    <p class="section-eyebrow">Tech stack</p>
    <h1 class="page-hero-title">
      Palchat Tech Stack
    </h1>
    <p class="page-hero-subtitle" style="margin: var(--sp-3) auto 0;">
      Building a fast, private, reliable chat platform for Palestinians — March 2026 edition.
    </p>
    <p
      class="body-text"
      style="
          max-width: 640px;
          margin: var(--sp-3) auto 0;
        "
    >
      Minimal, performant choices that let us ship quickly without managing servers or heavy infrastructure.
    </p>
  </div>
</section>

<!-- Layer flow diagram -->
<section class="section" style="padding-top: var(--sp-7); padding-bottom: var(--sp-7);">
  <div class="app-container">
    <header style="text-align: center; margin-bottom: var(--sp-5);">
      <h2 class="section-title">
        From visitor to database, in one line
      </h2>
      <p
        class="body-text"
        style="
            max-width: 640px;
            margin: var(--sp-3) auto 0;
          "
      >
        A simple, end‑to‑end path for every request — keeping latency low and moving parts understandable.
      </p>
    </header>

    <div
      class="flex flex-col items-stretch gap-3 text-sm sm:flex-row sm:items-center sm:justify-center sm:gap-4"
      aria-label="High-level Palchat architecture flow"
    >
      <div
        class="inline-flex items-center justify-center rounded-full border border-[var(--color-border)] bg-[var(--color-bg)] px-4 py-2"
      >
        <span class="body-text-small" style="font-weight: 600; color: var(--color-text-primary);">
          Visitor / Browser
        </span>
      </div>

      <span class="hidden text-sm text-[var(--color-text-secondary)] sm:inline" aria-hidden="true">
        →
      </span>

      <div
        class="inline-flex items-center justify-center rounded-full border border-[var(--color-border)] bg-[var(--color-bg)] px-4 py-2"
      >
        <span class="body-text-small" style="font-weight: 600; color: var(--color-text-primary);">
          Frontend (Astro + React islands)
        </span>
      </div>

      <span class="hidden text-sm text-[var(--color-text-secondary)] sm:inline" aria-hidden="true">
        →
      </span>

      <div
        class="inline-flex items-center justify-center rounded-full border border-[var(--color-border)] bg-[var(--color-bg)] px-4 py-2"
      >
        <span class="body-text-small" style="font-weight: 600; color: var(--color-text-primary);">
          Edge APIs (Vercel Functions)
        </span>
      </div>

      <span class="hidden text-sm text-[var(--color-text-secondary)] sm:inline" aria-hidden="true">
        →
      </span>

      <div
        class="inline-flex items-center justify-center rounded-full border border-[var(--color-border)] bg-[var(--color-bg)] px-4 py-2"
      >
        <span class="body-text-small" style="font-weight: 600; color: var(--color-text-primary);">
          Database (PostgreSQL)
        </span>
      </div>

      <span class="hidden text-sm text-[var(--color-text-secondary)] sm:inline" aria-hidden="true">
        →
      </span>

      <div
        class="inline-flex items-center justify-center rounded-full border border-[var(--color-border)] bg-[var(--color-bg)] px-4 py-2"
      >
        <span class="body-text-small" style="font-weight: 600; color: var(--color-text-primary);">
          Hosting & CDN (Vercel)
        </span>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<!-- Stack by layer -->
<section class="section-tight" style="padding-top: 0; padding-bottom: var(--sp-8);">
  <div class="app-container">
    <header style="text-align: center; margin-bottom: var(--sp-6);">
      <h2 class="section-title">
        Stack by layer
      </h2>
      <p
        class="body-text"
        style="
            max-width: 640px;
            margin: var(--sp-3) auto 0;
          "
      >
        Every part of Palchat is intentionally small, understandable, and biased toward fast first paint and low latency.
      </p>
    </header>

    <div class="grid gap-6 md:grid-cols-3">
      <!-- Frontend card -->
      <article
        class="card group flex flex-col gap-4 border border-[var(--color-border)] transition-colors duration-150 hover:border-[var(--color-primary)]"
      >
        <header class="flex items-center gap-3">
          <div
            class="flex h-9 w-9 items-center justify-center rounded-full border border-[var(--color-border)] bg-[var(--color-bg)]"
          >
            <span
              class="text-xs font-semibold"
              style="font-family: 'JetBrains Mono', monospace; color: var(--color-text-primary);"
            >
              FE
            </span>
          </div>
          <div>
            <p class="section-eyebrow">
              Layer 1
            </p>
            <h3
              class="section-title"
              style="
                  font-size: 1.25rem;
                  margin-top: var(--sp-1);
                "
            >
              Frontend
            </h3>
          </div>
        </header>

        <ul class="mt-2 space-y-4">
          <li class="flex items-start gap-3">
            <div
              class="mt-0.5 flex h-8 w-8 flex-shrink-0 items-center justify-center rounded-full border border-[var(--color-border)] bg-[var(--color-bg)]"
            >
              <span
                class="text-[11px] font-semibold"
                style="font-family: 'JetBrains Mono', monospace; color: var(--color-text-primary);"
              >
                Astro
              </span>
            </div>
            <div class="space-y-1">
              <p class="body-text-small" style="color: var(--color-text-primary); font-weight: 500;">
                Astro
                <span style="font-weight: 400; color: var(--color-text-secondary);">
                  — fast, mostly static pages with excellent performance.
                </span>
              </p>
              <p
                class="body-text-small"
                style="font-size: 0.75rem; color: var(--color-text-secondary);"
              >
                <span style="font-weight: 500;">Why:</span> Ships almost zero JavaScript by default, so even on slow
                connections first paint stays comfortably under sub‑second budgets.
              </p>
            </div>
          </li>

          <li class="flex items-start gap-3">
            <div
              class="mt-0.5 flex h-8 w-8 flex-shrink-0 items-center justify-center rounded-full border border-[var(--color-border)] bg-[var(--color-bg)]"
            >
              <span
                class="text-[11px] font-semibold"
                style="font-family: 'JetBrains Mono', monospace; color: var(--color-text-primary);"
              >
                React
              </span>
            </div>
            <div class="space-y-1">
              <p class="body-text-small" style="color: var(--color-text-primary); font-weight: 500;">
                React islands
                <span style="font-weight: 400; color: var(--color-text-secondary);">
                  — only where real interactivity is required.
                </span>
              </p>
              <p
                class="body-text-small"
                style="font-size: 0.75rem; color: var(--color-text-secondary);"
              >
                <span style="font-weight: 500;">Why:</span> Hydrates just the interactive pieces (like thoughts and tools),
                keeping the overall bundle tiny while still feeling modern.
              </p>
            </div>
          </li>

          <li class="flex items-start gap-3">
            <div
              class="mt-0.5 flex h-8 w-8 flex-shrink-0 items-center justify-center rounded-full border border-[var(--color-border)] bg-[var(--color-bg)]"
            >
              <span
                class="text-[11px] font-semibold"
                style="font-family: 'JetBrains Mono', monospace; color: var(--color-text-primary);"
              >
                TW
              </span>
            </div>
            <div class="space-y-1">
              <p class="body-text-small" style="color: var(--color-text-primary); font-weight: 500;">
                Tailwind CSS
                <span style="font-weight: 400; color: var(--color-text-secondary);">
                  — utility‑first styling wired to design tokens.
                </span>
              </p>
              <p
                class="body-text-small"
                style="font-size: 0.75rem; color: var(--color-text-secondary);"
              >
                <span style="font-weight: 500;">Why:</span> Rapid, consistent UI without fighting the cascade — every
                component stays aligned to the same spacing and color system.
              </p>
            </div>
          </li>
        </ul>
      </article>

      <!-- Backend card -->
      <article
        class="card group flex flex-col gap-4 border border-[var(--color-border)] transition-colors duration-150 hover:border-[var(--color-primary)]"
      >
        <header class="flex items-center gap-3">
          <div
            class="flex h-9 w-9 items-center justify-center rounded-full border border-[var(--color-border)] bg-[var(--color-bg)]"
          >
            <span
              class="text-xs font-semibold"
              style="font-family: 'JetBrains Mono', monospace; color: var(--color-text-primary);"
            >
              BE
            </span>
          </div>
          <div>
            <p class="section-eyebrow">
              Layer 2
            </p>
            <h3
              class="section-title"
              style="
                  font-size: 1.25rem;
                  margin-top: var(--sp-1);
                "
            >
              Backend
            </h3>
          </div>
        </header>

        <ul class="mt-2 space-y-4">
          <li class="flex items-start gap-3">
            <div
              class="mt-0.5 flex h-8 w-8 flex-shrink-0 items-center justify-center rounded-full border border-[var(--color-border)] bg-[var(--color-bg)]"
            >
              <span
                class="text-[11px] font-semibold"
                style="font-family: 'JetBrains Mono', monospace; color: var(--color-text-primary);"
              >
                VF
              </span>
            </div>
            <div class="space-y-1">
              <p class="body-text-small" style="color: var(--color-text-primary); font-weight: 500;">
                Vercel Functions
                <span style="font-weight: 400; color: var(--color-text-secondary);">
                  — small, focused APIs at the edge.
                </span>
              </p>
              <p
                class="body-text-small"
                style="font-size: 0.75rem; color: var(--color-text-secondary);"
              >
                <span style="font-weight: 500;">Why:</span> Single‑purpose serverless functions keep logic isolated, with
                cold starts typically under a couple hundred milliseconds.
              </p>
            </div>
          </li>

          <li class="flex items-start gap-3">
            <div
              class="mt-0.5 flex h-8 w-8 flex-shrink-0 items-center justify-center rounded-full border border-[var(--color-border)] bg-[var(--color-bg)]"
            >
              <span
                class="text-[11px] font-semibold"
                style="font-family: 'JetBrains Mono', monospace; color: var(--color-text-primary);"
              >
                Node
              </span>
            </div>
            <div class="space-y-1">
              <p class="body-text-small" style="color: var(--color-text-primary); font-weight: 500;">
                Node.js runtime
                <span style="font-weight: 400; color: var(--color-text-secondary);">
                  — familiar server logic in JavaScript.
                </span>
              </p>
              <p
                class="body-text-small"
                style="font-size: 0.75rem; color: var(--color-text-secondary);"
              >
                <span style="font-weight: 500;">Why:</span> Same language across frontend and backend reduces cognitive load
                and keeps deploys straightforward.
              </p>
            </div>
          </li>

          <li class="flex items-start gap-3">
            <div
              class="mt-0.5 flex h-8 w-8 flex-shrink-0 items-center justify-center rounded-full border border-[var(--color-border)] bg-[var(--color-bg)]"
            >
              <span
                class="text-[11px] font-semibold"
                style="font-family: 'JetBrains Mono', monospace; color: var(--color-text-primary);"
              >
                Mail
              </span>
            </div>
            <div class="space-y-1">
              <p class="body-text-small" style="color: var(--color-text-primary); font-weight: 500;">
                Nodemailer
                <span style="font-weight: 400; color: var(--color-text-secondary);">
                  — transactional email from serverless functions.
                </span>
              </p>
              <p
                class="body-text-small"
                style="font-size: 0.75rem; color: var(--color-text-secondary);"
              >
                <span style="font-weight: 500;">Why:</span> A small, battle‑tested library for contact flows and internal
                alerts without pulling in a full email service SDK.
              </p>
            </div>
          </li>
        </ul>
      </article>

      <!-- Data & infrastructure card -->
      <article
        class="card group flex flex-col gap-4 border border-[var(--color-border)] transition-colors duration-150 hover:border-[var(--color-primary)]"
      >
        <header class="flex items-center gap-3">
          <div
            class="flex h-9 w-9 items-center justify-center rounded-full border border-[var(--color-border)] bg-[var(--color-bg)]"
          >
            <span
              class="text-xs font-semibold"
              style="font-family: 'JetBrains Mono', monospace; color: var(--color-text-primary);"
            >
              DB
            </span>
          </div>
          <div>
            <p class="section-eyebrow">
              Layer 3
            </p>
            <h3
              class="section-title"
              style="
                  font-size: 1.25rem;
                  margin-top: var(--sp-1);
                "
            >
              Data &amp; infrastructure
            </h3>
          </div>
        </header>

        <ul class="mt-2 space-y-4">
          <li class="flex items-start gap-3">
            <div
              class="mt-0.5 flex h-8 w-8 flex-shrink-0 items-center justify-center rounded-full border border-[var(--color-border)] bg-[var(--color-bg)]"
            >
              <span
                class="text-[11px] font-semibold"
                style="font-family: 'JetBrains Mono', monospace; color: var(--color-text-primary);"
              >
                PG
              </span>
            </div>
            <div class="space-y-1">
              <p class="body-text-small" style="color: var(--color-text-primary); font-weight: 500;">
                PostgreSQL
                <span style="font-weight: 400; color: var(--color-text-secondary);">
                  — main relational database for thoughts, user accounts, sessions, and metadata.
                </span>
              </p>
              <p
                class="body-text-small"
                style="font-size: 0.75rem; color: var(--color-text-secondary);"
              >
                <span style="font-weight: 500;">Why:</span> Proven, durable storage that comfortably handles 100k+ messages
                per day with structured queries and proper indexing.
              </p>
            </div>
          </li>

          <li class="flex items-start gap-3">
            <div
              class="mt-0.5 flex h-8 w-8 flex-shrink-0 items-center justify-center rounded-full border border-[var(--color-border)] bg-[var(--color-bg)]"
            >
              <span
                class="text-[11px] font-semibold"
                style="font-family: 'JetBrains Mono', monospace; color: var(--color-text-primary);"
              >
                pg
              </span>
            </div>
            <div class="space-y-1">
              <p class="body-text-small" style="color: var(--color-text-primary); font-weight: 500;">
                `pg` pooled client
                <span style="font-weight: 400; color: var(--color-text-secondary);">
                  — safe database connections in serverless environments.
                </span>
              </p>
              <p
                class="body-text-small"
                style="font-size: 0.75rem; color: var(--color-text-secondary);"
              >
                <span style="font-weight: 500;">Why:</span> Connection pooling avoids exhausting database limits while still
                giving each function a clean, typed interface to Postgres.
              </p>
            </div>
          </li>

          <li class="flex items-start gap-3">
            <div
              class="mt-0.5 flex h-8 w-8 flex-shrink-0 items-center justify-center rounded-full border border-[var(--color-border)] bg-[var(--color-bg)]"
            >
              <span
                class="text-[11px] font-semibold"
                style="font-family: 'JetBrains Mono', monospace; color: var(--color-text-primary);"
              >
                V
              </span>
            </div>
            <div class="space-y-1">
              <p class="body-text-small" style="color: var(--color-text-primary); font-weight: 500;">
                Vercel (hosting, SSL, CDN)
                <span style="font-weight: 400; color: var(--color-text-secondary);">
                  — deploys, certificates, and edge caching out of the box.
                </span>
              </p>
              <p
                class="body-text-small"
                style="font-size: 0.75rem; color: var(--color-text-secondary);"
              >
                <span style="font-weight: 500;">Why:</span> Pushing to main triggers a full build and deploy: Astro pages are
                rebuilt, functions refreshed, and everything served securely from a global edge network.
              </p>
            </div>
          </li>
        </ul>
      </article>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

